# Docker Standards

- Use multi-stage builds for runtime images when feasible.
- Do not expose ports that are not required by app traffic or health checks.
- Use restart policies (`unless-stopped` or `always`) for production services.
- Pin explicit image tags; avoid `latest`.
- Keep runtime images lean (remove build tools and caches).
- Prefer environment variables and secrets over hardcoded credentials.
- Reference project manifests when editing: `@docker-compose.dev.yml`, `@docker-compose.prod.yml`.
